Blackstone May Buy Mint Hotels for $938 Million, Times Reports

-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 
2011-07-24T06:04:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/blackstone-may-buy-mint-hotels-for-938-million-times-reports.html
Blackstone Group LP (BX)  is close to
buying Mint Hotels for 575 million pounds ($938 million),
according to the Sunday Times newspaper, which didn’t disclose
where it got the information.  Blackstone, the world’s biggest private-equity firm, has
beaten rival TPG Capital to the acquisition, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adam Haigh in London at 
 ahaigh1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  